        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Controller_Router_Route trims slashes by default, which means that on a given website, these urls are equivalent :\r\n\r\n\/login\r\n\/login\/\r\n\/login\/\/\r\n\/\/login\/\/\r\n\r\nIMHO, this is quite a non desirable behavior, as :\r\n* It can break the layout if we use relative paths in the HTML (\/login & \/login\/ are not considered the same folder);\r\n* Having a resource accessible via multiple urls breaks one of the basic principles for SEO.\r\n\r\nWe cannot override that by providing our own routes, because of the file Zend\/Controller\/Router\/Route.php, on line 160 :\r\n$route = trim($route, $this->_urlDelimiter);\r\n\r\nI've created a thread on the official forum about this issue, but got no opinion from other users :\r\nhttp:\/\/forums.zend.com\/viewtopic.php?f=69&t=8750"
        },
